{"lemma":"دُرّاجُ","slug":"دُرّاجُ","root":"د.ر.ج","root_slug":"د-ر-ج","root_link":"/words/roots/د-ر-ج","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n12394","n12395"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%91%D8%A7%D8%AC%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cyclist, biker"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of دَرَج (daraj)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"phasanid, most commonly Francolinus francolin, but also Chrysolophus pheasant"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Occupational noun from the root د ر ج (d r j).\n\nIdentical to تَدْرُج (tadruj, “pheasant”); the first form based on Middle Persian *tadurug, the present form on the last two thirds of *tudurāg, with gemination in the Arabic word after the measure as found in عُكَّاز (ʕukkāz)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n12394","headword_ar":"دَرَّاجٌ","root":"drj","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One who creeps along"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yadoruju","text_ar":"يَدْرُجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with calumny,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slander, among people:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who calumniates,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slanders, much"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"frequently."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~ar~aAju","text_ar":"الدَّرَّاجُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The hedge-hog;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqunofu*u","text_ar":"القُنْفُذُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) because he creeps along all the night: an epithet in which the quality of a subst. predominates. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abuw dar~aAjK","text_ar":"اَبُو دَرَّاجٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain small bird."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["A","K"]},{"entry_id":"n12395","headword_ar":"دُرَّاجٌ","root":"drj","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain bird,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) [the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"attagen, francolin, heath-cock,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rail,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"resembling the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayoquTaAn","text_ar":"حَيْقُطَان"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and of the birds of El-'Irák, marked with black and white spots,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to the T,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spotted:"},{"kind":"text","text":"IDrd says, I think it is a post-classical word; and it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the same as the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"durajap","text_ar":"دُرَجَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dur~ajap","text_ar":"دُرَّجَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": in the S it is said that the names"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dur~aAjN","text_ar":"دُرَّاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dur~aAjapN","text_ar":"دُرَّاجَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"are applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"male"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female"},{"kind":"text","text":"[respectively] until one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayoquTaAn","text_ar":"حَيْقُطَان"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is applied peculiarly to the male. (TA.) [See also De Sacy's “ Chrest. Ar. ” 2nd ed. ii. 39.]"}],"source_refs":["S","K"]}]}}